## Frequently Asked Questions

### How much does a 6 carat round diamond cost in {{year}}?

A natural GIA Excellent 6ct round diamond starts at $187,650 on Blue Nile for a G-VS2 grade and reaches $433,900 for a D-FL. Lab-grown IGI D-VVS1 6ct Excellent starts at $18,410. There is no natural GIA Excellent 6ct round under $180,000 on the open market.

### How big is a 6 carat round diamond in millimeters?

A 6ct round brilliant measures approximately 11.7mm in face-up diameter — 83% wider than a 1ct stone at 6.4mm. The face-up area is approximately 107 mm², which is 3.3× the face-up area of a 1ct round. On a size-6 finger, a 6ct stone covers 71% of the finger's visible width.

### What is the per-carat price of a 6ct round diamond?

A G-VS2 GIA Excellent 6ct round costs approximately $31,100 per carat, compared to $3,230 per carat for a 1ct G-VS2 — a 9.6× multiple. This premium is structural: GIA Excellent 6ct rounds number only 12–16 on Blue Nile at any time versus 400–600 at the 1ct level.

### Should I buy GIA or IGI for a natural 6ct round diamond?

GIA only. IGI's grade inflation — approximately 1–2 color grades and 1 clarity grade looser than GIA — compounds at large sizes. An IGI G-VVS1 natural 6ct may correspond to H-VS1 at GIA. At 11.7mm, H color in white gold is visible to the naked eye. Paying over $190,000 for a stone that presents as H color is not a value purchase.

### Is VS2 clarity eye-clean in a 6ct round diamond?

Yes. Round brilliant cuts distribute light across 57 facets, which prevents VS2 inclusions from appearing as dark spots to the naked eye even at 11.7mm diameter. VS2 is the value sweet spot at 6ct. VS1 adds certainty but costs $10,000–$15,000 more for a clarity difference undetectable without magnification. VVS adds $75,000–$90,000 for no visible benefit.

### Is a 6ct lab-grown diamond worth buying?

Yes, for visual impact. A lab-grown 6ct D-VVS1 IGI Excellent at $18,410 is physically identical to a natural 6ct in face-up appearance and optical performance. The real difference is resale: natural 6ct resells at 40–50% of retail ($75,000–$94,000); lab-grown resells at 10–20% ($1,800–$3,700). Choose natural for the asset. Choose lab for the diamond.

### What color should I choose for a 6ct round diamond?

G in white gold. D, E, and F add $40,000–$246,000 over G for color that is invisible face-up in a mounted ring, because the round brilliant's light return overwhelms subtle color differences at any face-up size. In yellow or rose gold, H is sufficient — yellow metal neutralizes trace warmth in the stone.

### How does a 6ct compare to a 5ct round diamond in size and price?

A 6ct is approximately 0.7mm wider than a 5ct face-up (11.7mm vs 11.0mm) — a 6.4% diameter increase that adds 13% to face-up area. The price jump is $40,000–$75,000 depending on quality: the natural 5ct entry starts at $147,110, while the natural 6ct entry starts at $187,650. Per-carat pricing is similar at both sizes (~$30,000–$31,000/ct for G-VS2) because scarcity is fully priced in by the 5ct level.

### What ring setting works best for a 6ct round diamond?

A four- or six-prong solitaire in platinum or 18K white gold lets the stone lead. Six prongs are more secure at 11.7mm. Avoid pave or halo settings that add visual noise around a stone this large. For active daily wear, a bezel offers the most protection. Yellow gold warms even G color at 6ct; use platinum if colorlessness matters.

### What is the resale value of a natural 6ct GIA round diamond?

Natural GIA round diamonds at 6ct resell at approximately 40–50% of retail through auction channels. At the $187,650 entry price, expect $75,060–$93,825 at resale. D-FL collector-tier stones have deeper auction market liquidity and may achieve higher recovery in strong market conditions. Lab-grown 6ct resells at 10–20% of retail.

### Why are two GIA 6ct G-VS2 stones priced differently?

Two GIA 6ct G-VS2 Excellent stones at $187,650 and $206,360 carry the same grade but differ in proportions. GIA's Excellent category spans a range — table 53–58%, crown angle 32.7–36.0°, pavilion angle 40.6–41.8°. A stone at the optimal center of each range commands a premium over one that meets the Excellent threshold at the less desirable end. Always check every proportion point on the GIA certificate, not just the cut grade.

### How rare is a natural 6ct round diamond?

Very rare. Blue Nile typically lists 12–16 GIA Excellent natural 6ct round diamonds at any given time out of hundreds of thousands of loose diamonds. Suitable rough for a 6ct round represents less than 0.1% of global diamond production. Above 6ct, most serious collectors move from retail platforms to specialist brokers and private treaty sales.

